dspace-development.title: Troubleshoot and document the solution for authentication issues on the Symplectic Elements QA and Production environments

comments.body:
When requesting https://oar-dev.princeton.edu/rt4ds/repository, the OAR installation attempts to connect to the Elements server. This connection fails from within the OAR server environment with the following:

```bash
2020-10-27 09:40:21,047 ERROR uk.co.symplectic.elements.servlets.RepositoryServlet @ Caught ClientAbortException
org.apache.catalina.connector.ClientAbortException: java.net.SocketException: Connection reset
        at org.apache.catalina.connector.OutputBuffer.realWriteBytes(OutputBuffer.java:411)
```

Please note that this is a *separate* error from what is raised when the Elements server attempts to deposit a submission into the OAR installation.

The following is logged on the load balancer for the OAR server node when attempting to establish a request from the Elements Windows Server:

```
TLS handshake error: handshake failed: error:140260C1:SSL routines:ACCEPT_SR_CLNT_HELLO:no shared cipher: Invalid argument
```
https://github.com/libressl-portable/openbsd/blob/master/src/lib/libssl/ssl_err.c#L317 is the error code for this on the server side.
This is now blocked by https://github.com/pulibrary/dspace-development/issues/204

orangelight.title: Audit Figgy for coin field values being recorded in Figgy but not displayed in the catalog

comments.body:
### Data and scripts
**Catalog JSON, Figgy JSON, and python script (15MB):** [figgy-catalog-diff.zip](https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/files/5441105/figgy-catalog-diff.zip)

### Links
**Link to spreadsheet & notes:** [https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1mXR8-AcpkN6eeU1A2mTHQKRfcZWE85l93JseYK0ZY9U/edit?usp=sharing](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1mXR8-AcpkN6eeU1A2mTHQKRfcZWE85l93JseYK0ZY9U/edit?usp=sharing)

**maps figgy -> catalog:** https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/937a33a31dea90f76f1439698748b37d0f0403f1/app/resources/numismatics/coins/orangelight_coin_builder.rb#L37

**builds figgy coin decorator:** https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/blob/937a33a31dea90f76f1439698748b37d0f0403f1/app/resources/numismatics/coins/numismatics/coin_decorator.rb

### Diff process
- Gather all unique figgy keys (there are around ~300)
- Gather all unique catalog keys
- Strip solr suffixes
    - (Reduces the number of figgy keys to ~90)
- Find stripped figgy keys that aren't in the catalog
    - (reduces unaccounted figgy keys to ~50)
- Pair figgy keys with examples, and remove..
    - Keys that store internal info
    - Keys that were renamed when mapped from figgy to catalog
    - Keys that are a combination of other keys
    - Keys who have the same value for all coins (e.g. "claimed_by" is set to "principi" for entire numismatic catalog)
    - (reduces unaccounted figgy keys to ~15)

### Possible additions to coin UI

- Rights information
- Provenance
- Arks
- Loan information
- Numismatic sub-collection:
    - Unique values: Vermeule, Medals, Firestone, Bell, Antioch, Holzer, Ross Deposit 1, Savage, Museum, Donald, Phillips, Armenian Heritage, Ross, Wu, Near Eastern Studies, Schaaf, Maull, Latin Orient, RBSC
- Issue information: id & date info
- Numismatic artist, subject, and note (see below)

### Questions:

- [x] I assume that everything in the catalog json is displayed on the coin UI, is that a safe assumption? I expect it would take an hour to go through the ~70 keys.
- [x] I don't fully understand how figgy works with these. They are numismatic objects: Numismatics::Subject, Numismatics::Note, Numismatics::Citation, and Numismatics::Artist, but I can't find where they'd be mapped to the catalog.
    - For example, Artist ID `7955a4f5-6a12-4127-af52-f359831c626b` is mapped to [Coin 5232](https://catalog.princeton.edu/catalog/coin-5232), but there isn't any "Artist" in the UI.

No, not everything in the catalog JSON is displayed on the coin UI. All unique catalog keys are tracked on sheet 2 of the [notes spreadsheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1mXR8-AcpkN6eeU1A2mTHQKRfcZWE85l93JseYK0ZY9U/edit#gid=2055519906). 502 coins have the field `issue_artists_s`. It is not available through the UI. This was the only catalog field that wasn't displayed.
